<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1328,1534]" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Reiner-Drehwald, M. E." box="[289,564,1328,1354]" pageId="0" pageNumber="88" pagination="519 - 532" refId="ref1186" refString="Reiner-Drehwald, M. E. (2010) A taxonomic revision of Lejeunea deplanata (Lejeuneaceae, Marchantiophyta) from tropical America. Nova Hedwigia 91: 519 - 532. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1127 / 0029 - 5035 / 2010 / 0091 - 0519" type="journal article" year="2010">Reiner-Drehwald (2010)</bibRefCitation>
<taxonomicName box="[570,790,1328,1354]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Lejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="0" pageNumber="88" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="deplanata">
<emphasis box="[570,790,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">Lejeunea deplanata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
consists two varieties: 
<taxonomicName authority="var. deplanata" box="[1061,1376,1328,1355]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Lejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="0" pageNumber="88" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="variety" species="deplanata" variety="deplanata">
<emphasis box="[1061,1202,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">L. deplanata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[1264,1376,1328,1354]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">deplanata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Stephani 1914: 605) Reiner-Drehwald (2010: 529)" authorityName="Reiner-Drehwald" authorityPageNumber="529" authorityYear="2010" baseAuthorityName="Stephani" baseAuthorityPageNumber="605" baseAuthorityYear="1914" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Lejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="0" pageNumber="88" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="variety" species="deplanata" variety="cuspidata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">L. deplanata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[315,424,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">cuspidata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Stephani, F." box="[439,661,1364,1391]" pageId="0" pageNumber="88" pagination="449 - 704" refId="ref1427" refString="Stephani, F. (1914) Species Hepaticarum 5. George &amp; Cie, Geneve &amp; Bale, pp. 449 - 704." type="book chapter" year="1914">Stephani 1914: 605</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Reiner-Drehwald, M. E." box="[678,1015,1364,1391]" pageId="0" pageNumber="88" pagination="519 - 532" refId="ref1186" refString="Reiner-Drehwald, M. E. (2010) A taxonomic revision of Lejeunea deplanata (Lejeuneaceae, Marchantiophyta) from tropical America. Nova Hedwigia 91: 519 - 532. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1127 / 0029 - 5035 / 2010 / 0091 - 0519" type="journal article" year="2010">Reiner-Drehwald (2010: 529)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[1078,1126,1365,1391]" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">type</typeStatus>
specmens of 
<taxonomicName class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Cheilolejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="0" pageNumber="88" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="boliviensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">Cheilolejeunea boliviensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belong to 
<taxonomicName authority="var. deplanata" box="[383,710,1400,1427]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Lejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="0" pageNumber="88" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="variety" species="deplanata" variety="deplanata">
<emphasis box="[383,527,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">L. deplanata</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[598,710,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">deplanata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
owing to the lack of a filiform tooth of the leaf lobule (
<figureCitation box="[1366,1434,1400,1426]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,229,1353,1375]" captionTargetBox="[167,1418,196,1312]" captionTargetId="figure-24@1.[158,1428,184,1325]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Lejeunea deplanata Nees var. deplanata. A. Portion of plant with gynoecia, ventral view. B. Gynoecium, ventral view. C. Leaf, ventral view. D. Leaf lobule. E. Underleaf. F. Apical marginal cells of leaf lobe. G. Median cells of leaf lobe. H. Basal cells of leaf lobe. All from Herzog 3804 (isotype, JE)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5142849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5142849/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[136,358,1436,1462]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Lejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="0" pageNumber="88" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="deplanata">
<emphasis box="[136,358,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">Lejeunea deplanata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widespread in tropical America and is known from 
<collectingCountry isEnumeration="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">
<collectingCountry box="[969,1054,1436,1462]" name="Bolivia" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1066,1179,1436,1462]" name="Colombia" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1190,1315,1436,1462]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry name="Dominican Republic" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">Dominican Republic</collectingCountry>
</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[253,346,1472,1498]" name="Ecuador" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(including the 
<collectingRegion box="[520,638,1472,1498]" country="Ecuador" name="Galapagos" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">Galapagos</collectingRegion>
Archipelago), 
<collectingCountry box="[808,901,1472,1498]" name="Jamaica" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">Jamaica</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[914,1002,1472,1498]" name="Mexico" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">Mexico</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1015,1107,1473,1499]" name="Panama" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">Panama</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1119,1170,1473,1499]" name="Peru" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">Peru</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1235,1350,1472,1498]" name="Venezuela" pageId="0" pageNumber="88">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
(Reiner- Drehwald 2010).
</paragraph>
